      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>According to R. Cowley, this is a collection of commentaries on Old Testament books (from Genesis to Ruth) in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic with parts showing great variability, 
               but also sharing a common core. 'The monk Yǝsḥaq', which appears to be the name of the compiler (<t:foreign xml:lang="gez"> ዘአስተጋባእክዎ፡</t:foreign>) of the work <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4117Interpretation">Interpretation and Symbolic Commentary on Genesis and
     Exodus (general record) element TEI with id LIT4117Interpretation</t:ref> 
               is mentioned in only one of the known witnesses (<t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb39">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 39</t:ref>.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
